commitResults.messageTitle: Remove methods for retrieving time and update unit testing
Create classes for storage, ui, parser and task list, and update test cache
Add javadoc comments, rename test methods
Fix violations of the coding standards and Git standards required.
commitResults.messageBody:
There are several violations of the coding standard.

A common standard followed is much better in the long run as it allows others to easily read and add to the code base.

Let's update the violations as such.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add a find command for users to use a keyword as a query.
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no good way to search for specific tasks.

A find command is more user-friendly than having to search through the entire list of tasks using the list command.

Let's update the command list by implementing this function.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bugs with junit tests and dependencies
commitResults.messageBody:
Junit tests have problems referring to the main module.

The bugs with the dependencies would render developers unable to properly test the main module.

Let's update the test module to fix the testing methods.

The project had no gradle support.

Working without gradle support could lead to inefficient testing.

Let's add gradle support to this project.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use CheckStyle to detect coding style violations
commitResults.messageBody:
There were minimal checks completed to ensure compliance with the coding standard.

Complying with the coding standard helps to make the code and documentation seem seamless.

Let's update the code with the changes needed to align with the coding standard.

There is no graphical interface for Duke.

Adding a graphical user interface makes it much more user friendly.

Let's add a graphical interface to improve the user experience.

There is no use of var-args in this project.

The use of varags can help to make applicable functions more flexible by allowing different numbers of arguments.

Let's update the project so that varargs is used where relevant.

Default pictures are used for user and Duke.

Replacing the default pictures with custom graphics helps to differentiate this Duke program from other chatbots.

Let's
* update the picture used to represent the picture
* update the picture used to represent Duke (the chatbot)

There are no assertions in the entire project.

Using assertions can help to document important assumptions that should hold at various points in the code.

Let's add assertions for various classes to ensure that assumptions hold true.

Some classes have suboptimal code quality, with long methods and deep nesting.

Improving the code quality can help with readability and reducing unsafe practices.

Let's make the changes to the code quality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add a way to view a date's schedule
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no way to get tasks for a specific date.

Adding a schedule command allows users to search for tasks chronologically.

Let's add a command to allow users to find tasks for a specific date.

The GUI uses the same colors for the user and duke. In addition, the pictures used look unprofessional.

Improving the GUI to make it more polished helps users to differentiate between user and duke messages and become more satisfied by the aesthetics.

Let's improve the GUI with better colors and images.

There is no guidance for users as to how to run the chatbot.

Adding a user guide helps to allow users to figure out what commands are available and how to use them.

Let's add the user guide.

The user guide in the docs folder is not updated.

Failing to update the user guide in the docs folder means the website displays no information.

Let's update the user guide in the docs folder.
